gomodel:SYNGO_2943  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Cortical interneurons from constitutive Dact1 mutant mice have fewer excitatory synapses on primary dendrites\"\n\nFig.4: \"Reduction of excitatory synapses in Dact1 mutant cortical interneurons is cell-autonomous\"\n- \"In summary, we found significant reductions in the number of excitatory synapses on cultured cortical interneurons from IDact1-KO mutants, in which only interneurons have lost Dact1, while the number of inhibitory synapses on these dendrites showed a non-significant trend toward reduced numbers. \"\n\nFig.5: \"Interneuron-specific Dact1 mutant mice (IDact1-KO) have fewer excitatory and inhibitory synapses along cortical interneuron dendrites\"\n- \"Interestingly, compared to results obtained in primary culture, in vivo there was a more pronounced and significant decrease (by ~23%) in the number of inhibitory synapses along dendrites of mutant interneurons compared to controls (co-localized inhibitory pre-synaptic (VGAT) and post-synaptic (Gephyrin) puncta: 3.62±0.30 per 10 um in IDact1-KO versus 4.69±0.43 in control, p=0.0471) (Figure 5F, G). For excitatory synapses, the results obtained in vivo were similar to in vitro: there were significant reductions (by ~28%) in the number of excitatory synapses along dendrites of mutant interneurons compared to controls (co-localized excitatory pre-synaptic (VGLUT1) and post-synaptic (PSD95) puncta: 4.62±0.64 per 10 um in IDact1-KO versus 6.42±0.52 in control, p=0.0368) (Figure 5F', G'). \". Experimental description: - \"All mice were deeply anesthetized and decapitated ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2943" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

